          ],
          "defaultServings": 4
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "infoPanel",
        "attrs": {
          "body": "3 cups (750ml) Massel vegetable liquid stock, heated.",
          "tone": "info",
          "title": "Also"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Place oil and half the butter in a pan over medium-low heat.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Cook leek, garlic and half the rosemary, stirring, for 6-8 minutes until soft.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Add rice, stirring to coat grains, then add wine and simmer for 1-2 minutes or until almost evaporated.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Stir in stock, a ladleful at a time, allowing each to be absorbed before adding the next.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Continue to cook, stirring constantly, for 20 minutes or until al dente (you may not need all the stock).",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Stir in cream and cook for a further 2-3 minutes until warmed through.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Melt remaining 30g butter in a pan over high heat.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Cook mushrooms and remaining rosemary for 6-8 minutes or until mushrooms are golden. Season.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Serve risotto immediately, topped with mushrooms, brie and rosemary leaves.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Stir less. The agitation releases starch. You want some, but not all of it. Add a splash more stock at the end to loosen.",
              "cause": "Over-stirred, or too much rice for the stock.",
              "symptom": "Risotto is gluey"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Keep the stock at a simmer in a separate pan while you cook. Add another ladle and keep going, the rice tells you when it's done.",
              "cause": "Stock added too cold, or undercooked.",
              "symptom": "Rice still has a hard core"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Take the pan off the heat, beat in cold butter (mantecare), and let it stand for two minutes. It firms up as it rests.",
              "cause": "Last addition of stock was too much.",
              "symptom": "Risotto is too soupy"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Beat in cold butter and a fistful of grated parmesan off the heat. The fat carries the flavour.",
              "cause": "Stock was weak, or no finishing fat.",
              "symptom": "Tastes bland"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Variations",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Mushroom: add 30 g dried porcini soaked in warm water; use the soaking liquid as part of the stock.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Seafood: stir through cooked prawns and a handful of peas in the last two minutes.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Best fresh. Leftovers keep two days in the fridge; reheat covered with a splash of liquid.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The dish sits in the Italian home-cooking tradition: a few good ingredients, a long unhurried cook, and a pan that has fed the family for years. Worth keeping its roots in mind when you taste, the silence between flavours is part of the design.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
